{
  "stem": "24231.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, and then one side was open.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The side to the [NON-ENGLISH], which was the area where the transport used to come in, that was opened up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But otherwise, it was surrounded by moats with double walls.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the moat was in between.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were some little water in between and catacombs went through these.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a real, real old town, and it had barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was used as a military town and it had something like seven different barracks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I recall some of the names, Dresden, Hamlich Sudeten-Kaserne, and Jaeger-Kaserne, and Magdeburg-Kaserne.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "These were all barracks, military barracks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was in an area where the Czech section was bordering on the German-- on the German population, the Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Also, not far away was [NON-ENGLISH], which-- which in German, was [GERMAN], which was a pretty large Jewish, Jewish town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So the Germans built-- wanted to build a, a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Next to the town was a so-called [NON-ENGLISH], a little, little fortress, which was used as a prison for political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that was just, just bordering on a-- on a town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And so the Germans took these 1,000 guys, young guys, all of them are young guys in the beginning '20s, and-- to build up this house.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So what they were doing is cleaning out the barracks, putting bunks in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Then later on, the Germans moved out the population, because among the barracks there were also houses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So the population was moved out, and the whole town was converted into a, a ghetto, where only Jews were brought in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Next transport was AK2, which was another group of young guys that were helping out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then they started to ship and transport from all.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
